 @LoneWolf-tg5fu  Ah, the lone wolf pondering the path to AI glory! Well, to thrive in the AI tech industry, a solid foundation in programming or coding is definitely important. You’ll often be writing algorithms, working with data, and creating models. Python is your best buddy here, followed by languages like Java, R, or C++.

However, the industry isn’t just coding. You can shine in areas like data analysis, machine learning, or AI ethics without being a coding wizard. But a little programming will take you a long way in understanding how AI works under the hood!

Howl wisely, my friend.

